\begin{document}$${{\dot{V}}\hbox{O}_{2}}$$\end{document} kinetics not only for EFL exercise but also for control exercise [typically fitted by a mono-exponential function (Cunningham et al. 2000; Ozyener et al. 2001)], in order to allow adequate comparisons of relevant parameters of recovery for both exercise tests. Accordingly, the slow component observed after control exercise was not discernible in two subjects using the double-exponential function. This is in accordance with previously reported data by Cunnnigham et al. (2000) who exercised healthy subjects at a similar work rate (100 W), yielding similar exercise \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
